text.section:
Subsection (1) of this section shall not apply to interests in:
Industrial buildings, as defined under KRS 103.200, owned and financed by a tax-exempt governmental unit or tax-exempt statutory authority under the provisions of KRS Chapter 103, the taxation of which is provided for under the provisions of KRS 132.020 and 132.200;
Federal property for which payments are made in lieu of taxes in amounts equivalent to taxes which might otherwise be lawfully assessed;
Property of any state-supported educational institution;
Vending stand locations and facilities operated by blind persons under the auspices of the Office for the Blind, regardless of whether the property is owned by the federal, state, or a local government;
Property of any free public library; or
Property in Fayette County, Kentucky, administered by the Department of Military Affairs, Bluegrass Station Division.
